(setq register-alist '((107) (48 . #("--- Начало обработки изображений ---\nМодель: claude-3-7-sonnet-latest\nКаталог: langImg\nПрокси: http://127.0.0.1:12334\n------------------------------------\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-02-18 в 10.04.15.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted phrase from your image:\n\nWord/Phrase: calls on\n1. to call on\n2. To use or rely on someone or something; to make use of a resource, person, or service for assistance or support.\n3. Utilize, rely on, make use of, employ.\n4. Использовать, прибегать к, обращаться к, задействовать.\n5. The research paper #calls on# several scientific studies to support its thesis.\n\nIn this context, \"calls on\" refers to the function sort-cmp utilizing or making use of two auxiliary functions (isort and insert). This is a technical usage describing programming function relationships, where one function invokes or uses other functions during its execution.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-02-20 в 08.13.56.png ---\nLooking at the image you've shared, I can see text with the phrase \"barefaced bluff\" highlighted in blue. Let me explain this phrase:\n\nWord/Phrase: barefaced bluff\n1. barefaced bluff (noun phrase)\n2. An obvious or blatant deception or pretense that is made without any attempt to conceal it; a shameless or brazen falsehood.\n3. Obvious lie, blatant deception, shameless falsehood, outright fabrication\n4. Явная ложь, наглая выдумка, откровенный обман, бесстыдная ложь\n5. His claim of being an expert was a #barefaced bluff# that everyone could see through immediately.\n\nThe highlighting appears to be appropriate as \"barefaced bluff\" is a complete fixed expression that conveys a specific meaning about an obvious or shameless deception.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-02-20 в 08.18.08.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted word in the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: numerals\n1. numeral\n2. A symbol or character used to represent a number, particularly the standard digits (0-9) used in writing numbers in a decimal system.\n3. Digit, figure, number symbol.\n4. Цифра, числовой знак.\n5. In mathematics, we use Arabic #numerals# (0, 1, 2, 3, etc.) most commonly in everyday calculations.\n\nThe highlighting appears to be correct in this context, as \"numerals\" refers specifically to the symbols used to write numbers, which is precisely what the text is discussing in relation to base 10 representation.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-02-20 в 10.19.18.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted phrase \"percolate upward\" from the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: percolate upward\n1. to percolate upward\n2. To gradually move or spread upward through a series of levels or stages; in the context of the image, it refers to how values or information flow from lower nodes to higher nodes in a tree structure during evaluation.\n3. rise gradually, flow upward, ascend progressively\n4. постепенно подниматься, просачиваться вверх\n5. The innovative ideas from junior employees tend to #percolate upward# through the organization's hierarchy until they reach decision-makers.\n\nThe highlighting in the image appears to be appropriate as \"percolate upward\" forms a complete verbal phrase that conveys the specific meaning of gradual upward movement in the context of the tree structure being discussed.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-04 в 21.02.43.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted word \"accommodate\" from your image:\n\nWord/Phrase: accommodate\n1. to accommodate\n2. To provide sufficient space or capacity for; to adapt or adjust to meet specific needs or requirements; to make room for something.\n3. Make space for, adapt to, adjust for, make allowances for.\n4. Вмещать, приспосабливать, адаптировать, размещать.\n5. The new software was designed to #accommodate# users with various accessibility needs.\n\nThe context in your image shows this word is being used to describe how prefix notation can handle procedures with varying numbers of arguments, emphasizing its flexibility and adaptability.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-04 в 21.07.30.png ---\nI can see a fragment of text discussing mathematical expressions, with the phrase \"readily evaluate\" highlighted in blue. Let me explain this phrase:\n\nWord/Phrase: readily evaluate\n1. to readily evaluate\n2. To quickly and easily calculate or determine the value or result of something, without difficulty or hesitation.\n3. Easily calculate, promptly determine, effortlessly compute.\n4. Легко вычислять, быстро определять, без труда рассчитывать.\n5. The experienced mathematician could #readily evaluate# the complex equation in just a few minutes.\n\nThe phrase appears in the context of a mathematical expression written in prefix notation (Lisp-like syntax), which the text states would be calculated to equal 57 by an interpreter.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-06 в 10.16.20.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted word in the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: readily\n1. readily\n2. Quickly, promptly, and willingly; without hesitation or difficulty.\n3. Easily, promptly, willingly, without delay.\n4. Легко, охотно, без промедления, беспрепятственно.\n5. The new employees #readily# adapted to the company culture.\n\nThe word is correctly highlighted in the context of the text, which appears to be discussing different modes in the Vim text editor. In this context, \"readily\" indicates that Normal, Insert, and Visual modes are easily or immediately identified by users, in contrast to other Vim modes that might be less obvious or overlooked.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-06 в 10.27.30.png ---\nI'll explain the highlighted phrase \"percolate upward\" from the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: percolate upward\n1. to percolate upward\n2. To move gradually from a lower position to a higher one, typically referring to the movement of information, values, or effects through a hierarchical structure or system.\n3. Rise gradually, ascend progressively, filter upward\n4. Постепенно подниматься, просачиваться вверх\n5. Financial benefits from tax cuts often #percolate upward# through the economic system, eventually reaching larger corporations.\n\nIn the context of your image, it appears to be describing how values or data move through a tree structure in computing or mathematics, starting from terminal nodes (leaves) and gradually moving up through the hierarchy to higher levels where they are combined.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 14.25.14.png ---\nI'll help you analyze the highlighted text from the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: take\n1. to take\n2. An approach, interpretation, or perspective on a subject; a distinctive way of dealing with or understanding something.\n3. Approach, perspective, interpretation, viewpoint, angle.\n4. Подход, интерпретация, точка зрения, видение.\n5. Her unique #take# on the classic novel offers fresh insights that previous critics missed.\n\nIn this context, the word \"take\" refers to Vim's distinctive approach or interpretation of visual mode functionality, suggesting that while it serves a similar purpose to selection modes in other editing software, Vim implements it in a characteristically different way.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 14.39.32.png ---\nI see the image contains the word \"carry\" highlighted in blue within a text about Vim's Visual mode. Let me explain this highlighted word:\n\nWord/Phrase: carry\n1. to carry\n2. To continue, transfer, or extend something from one place, time, or context to another.\n3. Transfer, extend, convey, bring forward.\n4. Переносить, передавать, продолжать.\n5. The company hopes to #carry# the success of their first product into their new line of business.\n\nThe text appears to be discussing the functionality of Vim's Visual mode, explaining that it's \"just another mode\" and suggesting that behaviors from one context won't necessarily \"carry over\" to Visual mode as one might expect.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 14.46.42.png ---\nI can see a fragment of text with the phrase \"type out\" highlighted in blue. Let me explain this phrase:\n\nWord/Phrase: type out\n1. to type out\n2. To write or produce text by pressing keys on a keyboard, especially writing the full or complete version of something rather than using abbreviations or shortcuts.\n3. Enter completely, key in, write out in full.\n4. Напечатать полностью, набрать текстом.\n5. Instead of using the abbreviation, please #type out# the entire company name in the document header.\n\nThe highlighting appears to be correct for this phrasal verb, as \"type out\" is the complete expression.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 14.55.42.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted text in the image you shared.\n\nWord/Phrase: holds the hand\n1. to hold someone's hand\n2. In this context, it's a metaphorical expression meaning to provide excessive assistance or guidance to someone who lacks experience, treating them as if they need special help or accommodation.\n3. Coddle, baby, spoon-feed, pamper.\n4. Опекать, нянчиться, водить за ручку.\n5. The new programming course doesn't #hold your hand# - it expects you to figure out some problems on your own.\n\nThis phrase appears in the context of discussing Vim's Select mode, suggesting that this mode exists to accommodate users who prefer more conventional text editor behaviors rather than embracing Vim's modal nature. The author implies that Select mode is a concession to users who haven't fully adapted to Vim's distinctive approach to text editing.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 16.17.07.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted phrase from the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: route around\n1. to route around\n2. To find an alternative path or method to bypass or avoid an obstacle, problem, or limitation.\n3. Bypass, work around, circumvent, find a workaround\n4. Обойти, найти обходной путь, обходить\n5. Engineers had to #route around# the damaged section of the network to maintain connectivity.\n\nThe highlighted phrase \"route around\" is correctly highlighted in the context of the text, which discusses using an alternative approach (Normal mode operators) to overcome a limitation in Vim's Visual mode when working with the dot command. The phrase is used metaphorically to describe finding a solution that avoids a known problem.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-07 в 16.19.01.png ---\nI can see the highlighted phrase \"falls short\" in the text. Let me explain this expression:\n\nWord/Phrase: falls short\n1. to fall short\n2. To fail to meet a goal, standard, or expectation; to be inadequate or insufficient.\n3. Fail to meet expectations, be inadequate, be insufficient, come up short.\n4. Не соответствовать ожиданиям, не достигать цели, недотягивать.\n5. Despite all their preparation, the team's performance #fell short# of what was needed to win the championship.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-08 в 16.49.39.png ---\nI notice you've shared what appears to be instructions for a task involving explaining highlighted words from images, but I don't see an actual image with highlighted text in your message. The visible text in your message is incomplete and appears to be a fragment about CSS.\n\nIf you'd like me to explain highlighted words or phrases from an image, please share the image that contains the highlighted text, and I'll be happy to provide explanations according to the format you've specified.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-08 в 19.09.53.png ---\nI'll explain the highlighted word in the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: begat\n1. to beget\n2. To procreate or produce as offspring; a biblical/archaic term meaning \"to father\" or \"to produce\". In computing context, it refers to one program or language giving rise to another.\n3. Fathered, produced, generated, created.\n4. Породил, произвел на свет, создал.\n5. The ancient programming language BCPL #begat# C, which eventually led to many modern programming languages.\n\nThis image appears to be a humorous play on biblical language (\"X begat Y\") applied to the history of Unix text editors. It's mimicking the genealogical passages found in religious texts, but instead tracing the lineage of text editors: ed → ex → vi → Vim.\n\nThe highlighted word \"begat\" is used correctly in this context, maintaining the biblical style to create a joke about the evolution of Unix text editors.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-08 в 19.10.44.png ---\nThe image shows a text fragment discussing Unix text editors, with the word \"DNA\" highlighted in blue. Let me explain this highlighted term:\n\nWord/Phrase: DNA\n1. DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid)\n2. In this context, it's used metaphorically to refer to the fundamental characteristics, core elements, or essential features that were present in early Unix text editors and continue to exist in modern Vim.\n3. Core, essence, fundamental structure, genetic makeup\n4. Основа, сущность, фундаментальная структура, генетический код\n5. The #DNA# of the company's culture remained unchanged despite the many leadership transitions.\n\nThe highlighted term is used figuratively here to explain how the essential characteristics or \"genetic code\" of early Unix text editors has been preserved and carried forward in the modern Vim text editor.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-08 в 22.15.22.png ---\nI'll analyze the highlighted phrase from the image you shared.\n\nWord/Phrase: long range\n\n1. long range (adjective phrase)\n\n2. Operating or effective over great distances; covering or affecting things at a considerable distance; designed for use over extended distances. In the context of commands in the Ex text editor, it refers to commands that can affect text far beyond the immediate visible area or current line.\n\n3. far-reaching, extensive, broad-scope, wide-ranging\n\n4. дальнего действия, дальнобойный, далеко идущий, масштабный\n\n5. The military developed #long range# missiles that could strike targets thousands of miles away.\n\nThe highlighting appears to be correct as \"long range\" is a complete adjectival phrase in this context. The text is discussing characteristics of Ex editor commands, describing them as having the ability to affect text across many lines at once rather than just locally.\n\n--- Результат для: Снимок экрана 2025-04-08 в 22.39.23.png ---\nI'll help you explain the highlighted word from the image:\n\nWord/Phrase: brittle\n1. brittle\n2. Easily broken, cracked, or snapped; fragile and liable to break or shatter, especially when subjected to pressure or stress.\n3. Fragile, breakable, delicate, friable.\n4. Хрупкий, ломкий, непрочный.\n5. The old documents were so #brittle# that they had to be handled with special gloves to prevent damage.\n\nIn the context shown in the image, \"brittle\" appears to be describing something (possibly a programming or technical solution) that works but is not robust - meaning it might easily fail under certain conditions or is not flexible enough for different scenarios.\n\n---\n--- Обработка завершена ---\nУспешно обработано: 19\nОшибок: 0\nРезультаты в файле: langImg.txt\n" 0 14882 (yank-handler (evil-yank-line-handler nil t))))))
